SHORTCUTS

1. If you have your cursor on a line, just use ctrl + c and ctrl + v to copy the line
2. Alt + arrow keys to move lines easily
3. Alt + shift + arrows: make changes on all thoes lines of code
4. Press Crl + d to highlight a word, and then the next instance. You can manipulate all instances this way
5. Ctrl + p is search for files
6. Ctrll + / comment out a line